                            <comment id="12583788" author="stack" created="Mon, 31 Mar 2008 18:30:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Here is one means of telling if the CORRUPT HDFS is an instance of this issue:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
# ./bin/hadoop fsck -files /|grep -v &apos;OK&apos;| grep  -v &apos;&amp;lt;dir&amp;gt;&apos; /hbase/log_192.168.105.15_1206946790035_60020/hlog.dat.000 0 bytes, 1 block(s):  MISSING 1 blocks of total size 0 B
Status: CORRUPT
..
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If the only files output are log files missing 1 block and their reported of zero size, then its this issue.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12588717" author="stack" created="Mon, 14 Apr 2008 19:04:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This looks like &quot;New files under lease (before close) still shows up as MISSING files/blocks in fsck&quot; &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HADOOP-2703&quot; title=&quot;New files under lease (before close) still shows up as MISSING files/blocks in fsck&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HADOOP-2703&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HADOOP-2703&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
